The Board of Directors shall have the authority:

To prepare and issue rules and regulation as it considers necessary for the effective discharge of its responsibilities;

To direct the management, operations and administration of the Corporation;

To appoint, fix the remunerations and remove all officers and employees of the Corporation, subject to the Civil Service Law; and

To authorize such expenditures by the Corporation as are in the interest of the effective administration and operation of the Corporation.
